definitions.definition: To annul by an authoritative act; to abolish by the authority of the maker or their successor ; to repeal ; — applied to the repeal of laws, decrees, ordinances , the abolition of customs, etc.
definitions.dating_raw: First attested in the early 16 century.

definitions.definition: To put an end to; to do away with.
definitions.dating_raw: First attested in the early 16 century.

definitions.definition: To block a process or function.
